A 42-year-old woman was arrested for allegedly stabbing her husband to death in Mokwakwaila outside Tzaneen. Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said this happened after she reportedly found him with another woman in their house at Kuranta village. It is alleged that the mother of his two children unexpectedly arrived at the home and found them in the house. Mojapelo said an argument ensued between the two women and the deceased tried to intervene when the suspect allegedly stabbed him with a sharp object. The victim, aged 43, was taken to the local clinic where he was certified dead. The police were called, and the woman was arrested. She will appear in the Bolobedu Magistrate's Court tomorrow facing a charge of murder.